content: The data in Salesforce objects is normalized, meaning that it’s stored efficiently in a collection of related tables to minimize redundancy, enhance consistency, and ensure data integrity. In contrast, data in datasets is denormalized, where it’s stored in an optimal format for querying. All the work required to combine the data from multiple sources is done ahead of time. The data is centralized, compressed, and ready to be analyzed.
title: Understanding Denormalized Data in Salesforce
